{"word":"Ἰσκαριώθ","slug":"Ἰσκαριώθ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Ἰσϰαριώϑ</el></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ indecl.\">indecl.</a> and <b><el>Ἰσϰαριώτης, ου, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁ\">ὁ</a></el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> uncertain] <b>Iscariot,</b> surname of the informer Judas and also of the latter’s father (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Ἰούδας\">Ἰούδας</a></el> 6)<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> -<el>ώϑ</el>: <b><a href='B:480 3:19'>Mk 3:19</a>; <a href='B:480 14:10'>14:10</a>; <a href='B:490 6:16'>Lk 6:16</a>; <a href='B:490 22:47'>22:47</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b>-<el>ώτης</el> <b><a href='B:470 10:4'>Mt 10:4</a></b> and all other <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pass.\">pass.</a> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἴσθι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἴσος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}